result.execSummary:
The defendant Quienterrio O. Henderson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes:
Conditions:

Submit to AODA and follow through with all recommendations.

Pay costs.  If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due. All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.

Do no drive unless lawfully licensed.

Provide DNA sample at the Richland County Sheriff's Department before signing up for probation.

Parties stipulate to 0 days credit in the event of revocation.

Defendant Quienterrio O. Henderson in court with attorney Adrian Wayne Longacre. Prosecuting Atty Jennifer M. Harper appeared for State of Wisconsin.  Initial appearance in 15CM166 and plea/sentencing in 15CM123.  Counsel inform the Court that the parties have reached an agreement in both matters; def to plead to count 1/bail jumping in 15CM166 and to count 1/thc and count 2/drug para. in 15CM123, for dismissal/read-in of remaining counts and probation of 2 years with condition of no driving unless lawfully licensed.  Def pleads no contest to count 1 of 15CM166 and to counts 1 and 2 of 15CM123.  Court's colloquy re pleas.  Finding of guilty.  Sentence withheld for 2 years probation with conditions to include AODA and follow through; costs as a condition of probation; no driving unless properly licensed.  DNA sample to be provided.  OAR charges dismissed/read-in.

0 days credit.
